text:
Their team got so lucky that they decided to "practice" on the low-level looking wooden house, as Peko had deliberately made it look very unimportant with an iron doored core to hide her goodies of world destruction.

I think Peko had planned on angering everyone with that supply of C4 and then reverting to her personal Pentagon base lol and take on everyone, but now it gave her enemies tons of supplies to really challenge her and I'm glad Peko still managed to do the "team up with many, anger em with a rocket betrayal" play and then enact her plan which seemed to definitely be to retract into her base.
Everything about the war played out really perfectly.

Gura's aim was really great, I loved the mechanic of Gura pressuring Peko with sniping from the side and she played the part of applying sniper pressure in the team very well.. (Regarding Polka/Miko/Luna/Matsuri base attack too, where they couldn't stay on the roof fending them off due to Gura's quite persistent shots)

Also loved the moment where she called for Sui and restocked her with the spare AK and her supplies that she hadn't managed to stash at Sui's house due to the door code issues (stream brain and forgetting how to input the code at the lock hehe)

Even considering the language barrier, she played so well with em. Proud of our beloved shork <3

text:
Not gonna lie, I'm a bit disappointed in myself here. I knew that there was gonna be a season finale for Rust and that many EN were participating... but I had no idea it was going to be at 6AM (Calli apparently had it scheduled for this time slot, but it completely flew under my radar). I would have gladly set my alarm for this event if I knew it was going to be this early. But it seems all of the stream rooms and tweets went up at like 3am, while I was sleeping... :_GuraCry:

And what really sucks is that I actually woke up early out of a dead sleep and just checked my phone and saw no notifications that anyone was live. Either from YT or Discord (I don't know what's up with that...). So I went back to sleep. Then the next time I woke up, I was greeted to Gura already streaming for over 3 hours and Ame streaming for 6. 

I got a large set of vods to catch up on now, I guess. I just gotta wait for the livechat to finish processing. 

But, from the looks of things, it seems like this must have been a fun time, so I'm excited to catch up.
